# FE Cursor Guide

## Scope
- Apply these rules for any work under `FE/**`.

## Core Stack
- Keep frontend code in TypeScript + React patterns already used in `FE/src`.
- Reuse existing UI primitives from `FE/src/components/ui` before adding new components.
- Prefer domain-based placement under `FE/src/domains/*` and keep feature logic colocated.

## Styling and Tokens
- Use design tokens from `FE/src/index.css`; avoid hardcoded colors when a token exists.
- Keep existing flat-solid visual style (no new gradients unless explicitly requested).
- Preserve accessibility states (`focus-visible`, reduced-motion behavior, contrast-safe text).

## Color Switch (Must Preserve)
- Theme state source of truth is `FE/src/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx`.
- Keep `localStorage` key as `app-theme` unless migration is implemented.
- Keep both theme hooks in sync:
  - `document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', theme)`
  - `document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', theme === 'dark')`
- `ThemeSwitch` should call `toggleTheme` from context (no duplicate local theme state).
- If changing switch UI, preserve `aria-label`, `title`, and clear dark/light affordance.
- Any theme-token change in `index.css` must be checked for both default and `.dark` scopes.

## Routing and Auth Guardrails
- Respect existing route protection flow in `FE/src/App.tsx` (`RequireAuth`, `RequireRole`).
- Avoid introducing route-level behavior that bypasses auth/role guards.

## Quality Bar
- Keep edits minimal and targeted; avoid broad refactors unless requested.
- Prefer small reusable extraction over copy-paste in large pages.
- When changing theme/auth/routing behavior, include a short verification checklist in PR notes.
